    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-11-26T06:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-11-26T06:30:00-05:00" n="282"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <head>282. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in India</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d282fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 751K.00/11-2661. Secret; Priority; Limit Distribution. Repeated to
                        Saigon and to Geneva for <persName corresp="#p_HWA1"
                        >Harriman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>New Delhi</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1961-11-26T17:00:00+05:30">November 26, 1961, 5 p.m.</date>
                        </hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1501. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1500.<note n="2" xml:id="d282fn2"
                        >In telegram 1500, November 26, <persName corresp="#p_GJK1"
                            >Galbraith</persName> summarized his discussion that day regarding the
                        question of Viet-Nam and particularly the <gloss target="#t_ICC1"
                            >ICC</gloss> investigation of the Nam assassination. <persName
                            corresp="#p_GJK1">Galbraith</persName> observed that comments added
                        little to the picture that the Department of State already had of the Indian
                        Government’s views. (Ibid.)</note> … Hanoi had asked <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> if they could send Education Minister Tacha (phonetic spelling)
                    to New Delhi for confidential talks with <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> on
                        <gloss target="#t_VN1">VN</gloss> situation and threat to peace there…</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Unless there is penetrating and non-routine reason to contrary, I think I might
                    see Hanoi representative if and when he comes to New Delhi, and with appropriate
                    discretion hear what he has to say and indicate that while US and <gloss
                        target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> are not menacing and do not intend menace
                        <gloss target="#t_DRV1">DRV</gloss> we are serious in determination maintain
                    independence <gloss target="#t_SVN1">SVN</gloss>. Indians doubtless willing put
                    forward idea of meeting as their suggestion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJK1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Galbraith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
